A Makefile for Developing Containerized LaTeX Technical Documents:
- https://arxiv.org/abs/2005.12660

Requirements:
- POSIX-oriented operating system https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/POSIX#POSIX-oriented_operating_systems
- Git (Any version) https://git-scm.com/downloads
- GNU Make (>= 3.79) https://www.gnu.org/software/make/
- Docker (Any version or >= 19.03 for NVIDIA Container Toolkit) https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/
- [Optional] NVIDIA Container Toolkit https://docs.nvidia.com/datacenter/cloud-native/container-toolkit/install-guide.html

Preparation:
git clone https://github.com/pbizopoulos/a-makefile-for-developing-containerized-latex-technical-documents
cd a-makefile-for-developing-containerized-latex-technical-documents/
sudo systemctl start docker

Basic commands:
make		# Generate draft artifacts (fast).
make FULL=1	# Generate full artifacts (slow).
make clean 	# Remove artifacts/ directory.
make help	# Show all commands.
